name: The Call

description:
Sid Miller has accidentally killed the world's greatest hero. Now he needs to find out why.

When a drunken Sid Miller receives an anonymous text message asking “Should I kill myself?” his equally inebriated friends goad him into replying: “Yes”. The next day the world is shocked to discover the superhero Dark Justice has committed suicide.

A guilt-ridden Sid is press ganged by Black Fury (Dark Justice’s sidekick) into uncovering the truth behind the death. He’s forced to go ever deeper into the super-criminal underworld on a collision course with the last person to see Dark Justice alive: the masked psychotic Jack Slaughter.
Reprints political cartoons, Joe Bob Briggs and Ian Shoales columns, and comic strips: Calvin & Hobbes, The Far Side, Outland, Doonesbury, and Life In Hell (Matt Groening)
